The '''yellow-bellied bush warbler''' ('''''Horornis acanthizoides'''''), also known as the '''yellowish-bellied bush warbler''', is a [[species]] of bush warbler in the [[Family (taxonomy)|family]] [[Cettiidae]]. It was formerly included in the "[[Old World warbler]]" assemblage.

It is found on mainland China and Taiwan. [[Hume's bush warbler]] was formerly considered conspecific.

